1
00:00:15,182 --> 00:00:20,646
[man] <i>Both of them are carrying</i>
<i>some of these Rajneesh people from Oregon.</i>

2
00:00:20,729 --> 00:00:23,398
[man 2] <i>He is transporting bad guys.</i>

3
00:00:23,482 --> 00:00:25,150
<i>Hardened criminals.</i>

4
00:00:25,234 --> 00:00:27,402
<i>If he deviates</i>
<i>any from his route of flight,</i>

5
00:00:27,486 --> 00:00:30,405
<i>you got to let the president know</i>
<i>he's got an open line to security.</i>

6
00:00:30,489 --> 00:00:31,323
[woman]
<i>Okay.</i>

7
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:33,325
The search is on
throughout the Northwest tonight

8
00:00:33,408 --> 00:00:34,785
<i>for Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh.</i>

9
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:37,371
It became
fairly common knowledge out there

10
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:42,626
that the immigration service was about
to execute, uh, warrants for their arrest.

11
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:44,002
[male reporter]
<i>Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh,</i>

12
00:00:44,086 --> 00:00:46,505
easily the most controversial figure
in Oregon,

13
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:49,466
is in the middle of a controversy tonight
that he's not controlling.

14
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:52,219
Once we heard he was in the air
and was running,

15
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:53,971
your adrenaline takes over.

16
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:55,305
And it was just a matter of getting him--

17
00:00:55,389 --> 00:00:57,808
finding and getting him
and putting him in handcuffs.

18
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:01,478
[indistinct chatter over radio]

19
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:02,980
[Bill Callahan's "Drover" playing]

20
00:01:03,522 --> 00:01:05,774
<i>♪ I'll find a better way ♪</i>

21
00:01:07,234 --> 00:01:08,193
<i>♪ Someday... ♪</i>

22
00:01:11,113 --> 00:01:13,490
[male reporter] <i>The Coast Guard and FAA</i>
<i>have been tracking the two jets</i>

23
00:01:13,574 --> 00:01:16,868
<i>since they left Rajneeshpuram</i>
<i>about 5:30 this evening.</i>

24
00:01:18,287 --> 00:01:19,538
We got on phones

25
00:01:19,621 --> 00:01:23,166
and started trying to get hold
of the plane to tell them to turn around.

26
00:01:24,626 --> 00:01:30,716
Somehow, federal agencies were blocking
communication to the airplane.

27
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:35,345
We attempted for over four hours
to communicate with the plane,

28
00:01:35,429 --> 00:01:37,264
but no call was coming back.

29
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:42,352
I spent the evening listening to the news

30
00:01:42,436 --> 00:01:48,734
and getting periodic updates
from the U.S. attorney on his progress.

31
00:01:49,693 --> 00:01:52,237
[male reporter] <i>Frohnmayer said he wanted</i>
<i>to brief these high level officials</i>

32
00:01:52,321 --> 00:01:54,573
<i>from the White House</i>
<i>and Justice Department.</i>

33
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:57,451
This is a fortunate break, uh...

34
00:01:57,534 --> 00:01:59,453
but one that was,
in some ways, predictable.

35
00:01:59,536 --> 00:02:02,331
At least it was not unexpected
that he might try to fly.

36
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:06,084
[Weaver]
<i>We contacted the FAA to be informed.</i>

37
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:14,217
We were able to establish the fact
that they were heading to Bermuda,

38
00:02:14,301 --> 00:02:17,846
and Bermuda was selected
for one reason only, maybe two.

39
00:02:17,929 --> 00:02:18,764
<i>It's nice and sunny.</i>

40
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:22,267
<i>And secondly,</i>
<i>he was un-extraditable from Bermuda.</i>

41
00:02:22,351 --> 00:02:26,063
He would have
successfully escaped, uh, prosecution.

42
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:27,522
It was an interesting evening.

43
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:32,152
Uh, I don't think any of us knew
how that would end.

44
00:02:36,448 --> 00:02:40,077
[Weaver] <i>One plane was going</i>
<i>to refuel in Pueblo, Colorado,</i>

45
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:42,496
<i>and the other</i>
<i>was going to refuel in Salt Lake.</i>

46
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:46,875
<i>We found out that there was a significant</i>
<i>chance they were going to Charlotte.</i>

47
00:02:50,796 --> 00:02:55,884
<i>♪ Yeah, one thing</i>
<i>About this wild, wild country... ♪</i>

48
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:00,263
[female reporter]
<i>Rumors of a pending arrest intensified</i>

49
00:03:00,347 --> 00:03:01,598
<i>at the central Oregon ranch</i>

50
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:05,268
<i>after a Chicago Tribune reporter</i>
<i>saw Bhagwan and some disciples</i>

51
00:03:05,352 --> 00:03:06,645
<i>leave the ranch on Learjets.</i>

52
00:03:06,728 --> 00:03:08,605
<i>This was shortly before 5:30 p.m.</i>

53
00:03:10,232 --> 00:03:15,153
It was a little bit
like the low speed chase for OJ Simpson.

54
00:03:15,237 --> 00:03:21,201
It just didn't seem like there was
a plausible ending to that episode.

55
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:24,371
[Weaver] <i>So I got down on the floor</i>
<i>and looked at a map</i>

56
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:27,499
<i>to find out how many airports</i>
<i>were in the vicinity of Charlotte.</i>

57
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:31,086
<i>Special Agent LaDage</i>
<i>was able to contact another agent</i>

58
00:03:31,169 --> 00:03:33,922
<i>and they took up positions</i>
<i>at the Charlotte airport.</i>

59
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:35,590
<i>♪ Wasting my time ♪</i>

60
00:03:42,264 --> 00:03:46,309
I was at home on a telephone
talking to agents who were on the ground.

61
00:03:47,853 --> 00:03:51,648
<i>They were expecting that these people</i>
<i>in the plane might be heavily armed</i>

62
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:55,277
<i>and by the time the customs agents</i>
<i>and the Charlotte police arrived,</i>

63
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:59,114
they had every bit
as much firepower as the Rajneeshees.

64
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:06,705
<i>They staked out a position</i>
<i>and secured themselves...</i>

65
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:13,295
<i>and instructed the tower</i>
<i>to tell the planes when they landed</i>

66
00:04:13,378 --> 00:04:15,505
to come down to the place
that they had staked out.

67
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:17,966
[man]
Not for long.

68
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:20,802
But the planes didn't do that.

69
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:24,139
[male reporter] <i>Two Learjets carrying</i>
<i>Rajneesh and ten of his followers</i>

70
00:04:24,222 --> 00:04:26,475
<i>landed at the Charlotte airport</i>
<i>at 2:00 a.m.</i>

71
00:04:26,558 --> 00:04:29,102
<i>The U.S. Marshal Ray Abrams,</i>
<i>U.S. Customs agents,</i>

72
00:04:29,186 --> 00:04:31,688
<i>local and airport police</i>
<i>were waiting for the guru.</i>

73
00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:35,650
The planes proceeded to, one
then another, to Butler aviation,

74
00:04:35,734 --> 00:04:38,487
and so the agents
had to race down the tarmac.

75
00:04:45,243 --> 00:04:46,703
And they got the jump on the planes.

76
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:49,247
They surrounded them,
pulled out their weapons,

77
00:04:49,331 --> 00:04:51,374
<i>told the pilots</i>
<i>to put their hands on the glass.</i>

78
00:04:52,334 --> 00:04:54,002
[pilot] <i>We were approached</i>
<i>by many vehicles</i>

79
00:04:54,085 --> 00:04:55,879
and these people started
piling out of these vehicles

80
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:58,673
with high-powered weapons and started
pointing these weapons at us.

81
00:04:58,757 --> 00:05:02,886
Cops everywhere, people with shotguns,
sawed-off shotguns, handguns...

82
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:06,973
telling the people to get out of planes
and put their hands up on their head.

83
00:05:07,057 --> 00:05:09,309
I just put my hands up
in the cockpit, you know?

84
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:13,021
And at that time I figured,
"I think we're in some kind of trouble."

85
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:18,068
The agents were able to bring everybody
off the plane without a shot being fired.

86
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:22,113
<i>Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh</i>
<i>was hiding behind the seat,</i>

87
00:05:22,197 --> 00:05:24,241
and I think Ron Taylor
found him behind the seat...

88
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:26,910
uh...

89
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:29,120
and was able to encourage him to deplane.

90
00:05:32,249 --> 00:05:34,709
<i>♪ I rose like a drover ♪</i>

91
00:05:34,793 --> 00:05:36,545
[indistinct chatter]

92
00:05:36,628 --> 00:05:38,797
<i>♪ For I am in the end the drover... ♪</i>

93
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:41,800
[male reporter]
<i>Rajneesh is presently in custody</i>

94
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:45,971
of the United States Marshals Service
in Charlotte, North Carolina.

95
00:05:46,054 --> 00:05:48,890
[Jane]
<i>We were sitting watching TV</i>

96
00:05:48,974 --> 00:05:52,978
in the holiday apartment
that we had in the Black Forest.

97
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:58,692
<i>We were watching footage</i>
<i>of Bhagwan walking across the tarmac</i>

98
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:01,152
in North Carolina in chains.

99
00:06:01,236 --> 00:06:03,780
We couldn't believe it.

100
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:08,451
[male reporter] <i>With $55,000 in cash,</i>
<i>guns, boxes of jewelry, and his throne,</i>

101
00:06:08,535 --> 00:06:12,080
<i>the Bhagwan and a handful of his followers</i>
<i>fled the ranch commune.</i>

102
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:14,583
<i>They got as far</i>
<i>as Charlotte, North Carolina,</i>

103
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:17,669
<i>where U.S. Marshals arrested Rajneesh</i>
<i>and 12 of his friends.</i>

104
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:22,382
At the same time, the doorbell rang
in the holiday apartment where we were.

105
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:26,303
Suddenly, our pension got raided

106
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:30,849
by FBI and German secret police.

107
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:35,312
The police officers informed us
that they had arrest warrants

108
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:40,817
<i>for Ma Anand Sheela,</i>
<i>Ma Shanti Bhadra, and Ma Prem Puja.</i>

109
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:45,363
The charge was attempted murder
of Bhagwan's physician.

110
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:49,451
My knees went out from under me.

111
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:53,288
[male reporter] <i>Two FBI agents began going</i>
<i>through Sheela's personal effects,</i>

112
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:57,417
<i>gathering evidence as they waited</i>
<i>for her extradition to the United States.</i>

113
00:06:58,168 --> 00:07:01,421
<i>♪ Wild, wild country... ♪</i>

114
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:05,675
Charges against Sheela
and two of her compatriots

115
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:08,345
<i>for attempted murder, conspiracy</i>
<i>to commit a murder, and assault.</i>

116
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:16,561
[male reporter] <i>The American authorities</i>
<i>have indicated they'll move rapidly</i>

117
00:07:16,645 --> 00:07:20,273
<i>to get both the Bhagwan and Sheela</i>
<i>back to Oregon to face charges...</i>

118
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:23,985
a reunion neither of them wants.

119
00:07:27,238 --> 00:07:29,074
Okay, I just have this one thing to say.

120
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:34,287
All I can say at this time is that
Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh is in custody

121
00:07:34,371 --> 00:07:37,582
on a federal indictment
in Charlotte, North Carolina.

122
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:41,336
Uh, the United States Attorney
for this district, Charles Turner,

123
00:07:41,419 --> 00:07:44,172
seeks to have him removed to this district

124
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:46,716
uh, to prosecute him
pursuant to that indictment.

125
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,218
The indictment is sealed.

126
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:51,304
It will remain sealed
until further order of the court.

127
00:07:51,388 --> 00:07:53,014
- That's all I have.
- [man] Can you tell us the charges?

128
00:07:53,098 --> 00:07:54,015
No, I can't.

129
00:07:54,099 --> 00:07:55,850
[man] How many other people
are named on the indictment?

130
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:58,520
[woman]
Had he been informed of the indictment?

131
00:07:58,603 --> 00:08:01,815
Is he arrested because of the charges
on the indictment or for illegal flight?

132
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:04,150
He's arrested for the charges
on the indictment. I'm sorry that's all.

133
00:08:04,234 --> 00:08:06,444
[woman] Was he informed of those charges?
Was he aware--

134
00:08:06,528 --> 00:08:07,362
Sorry that's all I have.

135
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:10,156
[man]
Watch your mic. Watch your mic.

136
00:08:10,949 --> 00:08:12,575
[male reporter]
What's the next step?

137
00:08:12,659 --> 00:08:13,535
We'll proceed.

138
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:17,706
We'll consider our available options
and take what legal steps are available.

139
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:22,794
[male reporter]
When will you start working on it?

140
00:08:23,044 --> 00:08:23,878
[Niren]
Now.

141
00:08:27,007 --> 00:08:28,633
[Weaver]
<i>I went to Charlotte.</i>

142
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:33,471
There was a little bit
of a circus atmosphere there.

143
00:08:33,555 --> 00:08:37,392
There were songs on the radio about
the Bhagwan was captured in Charlotte.

144
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:40,937
<i>There were T-shirts</i>
<i>being sold outside the courthouse.</i>

145
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:44,274
[man] Big seller, the hot pink there.
Everybody likes that one.

146
00:08:44,816 --> 00:08:46,735
[male reporter] <i>Rajneesh will spend</i>
<i>the next couple of days</i>

147
00:08:46,818 --> 00:08:48,486
<i>in a jail in Charlotte,</i>

148
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:51,990
<i>where people suddenly find</i>
<i>his name at the top of the news.</i>

149
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:54,325
I think his wealth
is really something else.

150
00:08:54,409 --> 00:08:58,204
It just blows my mind
that somebody can have 90 Rolls Royces.

151
00:08:58,288 --> 00:08:59,831
Isn't that how many he has?

152
00:08:59,914 --> 00:09:02,375
And two Learjets.
That's really impressive.

153
00:09:02,459 --> 00:09:03,835
It's a free country. I don't know.

154
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:06,046
If he's breaking the law,
I guess they should do something.

155
00:09:06,129 --> 00:09:08,465
If he's not,
I suppose they should leave him alone.

156
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,467
[male reporter]
<i>Inside the Mecklenburg County Jail,</i>

157
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,510
one of the offices looks
like a flower shop.

158
00:09:12,594 --> 00:09:15,847
These flowers have been streaming in here
since the Bhagwan arrived.

159
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:17,849
Some have even been sent to the sheriff

160
00:09:17,932 --> 00:09:21,478
by Bhagwan followers who appreciate
the kind of care he's been getting here.

161
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:25,732
[male reporter] <i>Bhagwan is held</i>
<i>in a third floor medical unit</i>

162
00:09:25,815 --> 00:09:28,026
<i>with half a dozen others behind this door.</i>

163
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:31,821
<i>Jailers say he moves about very little...</i>

164
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:35,909
<i>and, to deal with the noise of jail,</i>
<i>is using a set of earplugs.</i>

165
00:09:35,992 --> 00:09:41,414
He gets vegetarian food and medical care
from 24-hour nurses in his cellblock.

166
00:09:41,498 --> 00:09:44,125
[warden]
<i>Bhagwan's a very good prisoner.</i>

167
00:09:44,209 --> 00:09:45,960
<i>He's been very patient with us</i>

168
00:09:46,044 --> 00:09:49,923
and he's been very cordial
to all our treatment and everything.

169
00:09:50,006 --> 00:09:52,092
[male reporter]
He's a somewhat unusual prisoner for you?

170
00:09:52,175 --> 00:09:53,051
Very unusual.

171
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:55,929
He's one of the, I guess,
biggest we ever had.

172
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:03,895
[Niren]
<i>I actually was the only one</i>

173
00:10:03,978 --> 00:10:06,898
<i>who could go in</i>
<i>and talk to him who was a Sannyasin,</i>

174
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:08,525
<i>because I was his lawyer.</i>

175
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:11,653
<i>So I went in</i>
<i>and spent hours with him every day.</i>

176
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:16,199
<i>I mean here's this man who is</i>
<i>the most amazing presence on the planet.</i>

177
00:10:19,244 --> 00:10:20,578
<i>And he's in jail.</i>

178
00:10:21,162 --> 00:10:22,747
He's in jail.

179
00:10:22,831 --> 00:10:24,541
And I need to get him out.

180
00:10:26,209 --> 00:10:27,210
It's my job.

181
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:33,424
[male reporter] This is not normally
the way we see you dressed.

182
00:10:33,508 --> 00:10:36,719
Is it awkward or embarrassing for you?

183
00:10:36,803 --> 00:10:42,058
It is absolutely awkward and embarrassing

184
00:10:42,142 --> 00:10:46,604
because I'm absolutely innocent.
I have not done any crime.

185
00:10:46,688 --> 00:10:50,316
I will first fight and finish the case

186
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:54,654
because I still see
that the American Constitution

187
00:10:54,737 --> 00:11:01,578
is one of the most valuable constitutions
in the world.

188
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:05,665
And it will support me and my commune.

189
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:09,043
So I'm certain that I will win it.

190
00:11:10,545 --> 00:11:12,964
So there I am
in the lawyer's interview room

191
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:15,675
with him sitting on a chair
and me sitting on the floor.

192
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:18,636
He was...

193
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:21,139
He was unchained.

194
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:24,726
He was just the same as when he was
sitting in front of 10,000 people

195
00:11:24,809 --> 00:11:27,604
when he was sitting there
in prison dungarees.

196
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:37,113
And I would just sit there
and feel his presence and be renewed...

197
00:11:38,489 --> 00:11:39,741
uh...

198
00:11:40,283 --> 00:11:42,076
and then go out and get back at it.

199
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:50,209
[female reporter] <i>Last week, the Bhagwan</i>
<i>was indicted for immigration fraud.</i>

200
00:11:50,293 --> 00:11:53,922
<i>Authorities say he lied about</i>
<i>his intention to remain here permanently</i>

201
00:11:54,005 --> 00:11:57,592
<i>and arranged sham marriages</i>
<i>so followers could stay too.</i>

202
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:03,806
[Niren] <i>He was charged with a technical</i>
<i>immigration violation, marriage fraud.</i>

203
00:12:04,474 --> 00:12:09,354
<i>In the indictment,</i>
<i>almost everything was about Sheela,</i>

204
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:11,397
<i>almost nothing about Osho.</i>

205
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:13,441
But that's all they had.

206
00:12:14,317 --> 00:12:15,860
That's all they had.

207
00:12:15,944 --> 00:12:17,779
[camera clicking]

208
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:22,158
[Niren] <i>If he had not been a guru</i>
<i>and he was just some guy,</i>

209
00:12:22,241 --> 00:12:25,620
they would have put up
a decent bail and let him go.

210
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:28,957
If the religious leader is guilty
of all of the charges against him,

211
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:34,837
he faces a 175 years in prison
and up to $350,000 in fines.

212
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:38,758
The fact of it is the charges
that were brought against him

213
00:12:38,841 --> 00:12:41,719
are almost never criminally prosecuted.

214
00:12:41,803 --> 00:12:45,348
To seek to hold him in jail
pending these charges

215
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:48,393
is statistically almost unprecedented.

216
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:50,269
Um...

217
00:12:50,353 --> 00:12:53,231
What we are dealing
with is a political situation.

218
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:57,193
[Weaver] <i>We have a man who has now</i>
<i>been charged with multiple crimes,</i>

219
00:12:57,276 --> 00:13:01,072
fled the United States, abandoning
all his followers by the way,

220
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:02,782
he was aware of the charge

221
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:05,743
and was getting out the United States
before he got caught.

222
00:13:05,827 --> 00:13:09,998
The best precaution was to detain him,
return him to Oregon,

223
00:13:10,081 --> 00:13:11,666
and begin to deal with
the prosecution there.

224
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:13,084
That's what we're preparing for.

225
00:13:13,167 --> 00:13:14,919
[male reporter] What do you think
was the strength of your case?

226
00:13:15,003 --> 00:13:17,463
Well, the strength of our case
clearly was the fact

227
00:13:17,547 --> 00:13:21,551
that three days after a sealed indictment
was returned by the grand jury,

228
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:24,137
he leaves the ranch
for the first time in four years

229
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,347
and flies across country
in the middle of the night.

230
00:13:26,431 --> 00:13:27,473
[cameras clicking]

231
00:13:27,557 --> 00:13:30,435
[Weaver] <i>We were anticipating</i>
<i>a vigorous trial,</i>

232
00:13:31,102 --> 00:13:33,229
<i>and we had more evidence than we needed.</i>

233
00:13:45,324 --> 00:13:50,246
[Sheela] <i>I was arrested,</i>
<i>and we were brought to the nearest prison.</i>

234
00:13:50,329 --> 00:13:53,791
All three were housed in the same room.

235
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:55,710
<i>Me,</i>

236
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:56,753
<i>Puja,</i>

237
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:58,463
<i>and Shanti Bhadra.</i>

238
00:13:58,546 --> 00:14:03,092
<i>There were so many journalists</i>
<i>around this prison.</i>

239
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:06,304
[chatter in German]

240
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:13,019
These German police guys
were pulling out photos of me

241
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:15,354
<i>and I had to autograph them.</i>

242
00:14:16,439 --> 00:14:18,024
It was bizarre.

243
00:14:18,107 --> 00:14:24,614
The moment the German authorities
had left the room, the handcuffs went on.

244
00:14:25,448 --> 00:14:27,116
The leg chains went on.

245
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:30,828
The German police handed us over

246
00:14:30,912 --> 00:14:35,875
to American authorities
to take us to America.

247
00:14:36,918 --> 00:14:40,004
[male reporter] <i>Shanti Bhadra arrived on</i>
<i>a commercial airlines flight from Chicago,</i>

248
00:14:40,088 --> 00:14:42,423
<i>and she'll spend the night</i>
<i>at the Downtown Justice Center.</i>

249
00:14:42,507 --> 00:14:46,386
<i>Also due in tonight, Anand Sheela,</i>
<i>Bhagwan's former personal secretary.</i>

250
00:14:47,053 --> 00:14:50,306
[male reporter] <i>By the time she arrived</i>
<i>at a dark and foggy Portland airport,</i>

251
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:51,349
<i>she was handcuffed,</i>

252
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:54,644
<i>but still managed to smile for the crowd</i>
<i>of photographers clustered above.</i>

253
00:14:58,106 --> 00:14:59,315
[man]
All right.

254
00:15:03,361 --> 00:15:05,321
- I'll see you back in just a little bit.
- Okay. Take care.

255
00:15:05,405 --> 00:15:07,073
- Okay.
- Bye-bye.

256
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:10,034
This is the best lawyer in Portland.

257
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,912
[female reporter] <i>Jon, she seemed to be</i>
<i>smiling a lot today.</i>

258
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:15,748
<i>Do you really think she's enjoying</i>
<i>being back in the public eye?</i>

259
00:15:15,832 --> 00:15:19,127
Well, you saw the smile on her face
as she went into the courthouse today.

260
00:15:20,086 --> 00:15:21,421
[cameras clicking]

261
00:15:21,504 --> 00:15:24,549
[Tuttle] <i>Nobody could be happy</i>
<i>being in Sheela's situation.</i>

262
00:15:25,174 --> 00:15:27,343
<i>Prosecutors have brought</i>
<i>her back to Oregon</i>

263
00:15:27,427 --> 00:15:31,472
because they think they'll have her
staying here in prison for years to come.

264
00:15:31,556 --> 00:15:34,517
[female reporter] <i>Heavy security</i>
<i>surrounded the arrival in The Dalles</i>

265
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:38,646
<i>of 38-year-old Ma Anand Puja</i>
<i>and 40-year-old Shanti Bhadra.</i>

266
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:43,109
<i>They were arraigned in Wasco County</i>
<i>Circuit Court on attempted murder charges.</i>

267
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,531
[woman]
Good morning.

268
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:50,199
- Thanks.
- [man] Very pretty.

269
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:52,827
Did I tell you
I was going to be wearing tennies?

270
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:57,165
[Gary] <i>By the time I sat down with Sheela,</i>
<i>she was in federal custody</i>

271
00:15:57,248 --> 00:16:02,336
and agents brought her
and we spent an afternoon together.

272
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:08,468
<i>I was struck</i>
<i>by how small and unimposing she was</i>

273
00:16:08,551 --> 00:16:12,597
because she'd been a pretty big figure

274
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:16,767
in Oregon at the time
and frankly in my life.

275
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:18,186
Um...

276
00:16:18,269 --> 00:16:22,064
And she was completely forthcoming,

277
00:16:22,148 --> 00:16:23,566
answered all of my questions.

278
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:27,153
I believe she answered them
with complete honesty

279
00:16:27,236 --> 00:16:31,157
and with not the slightest trace
of shame or regret

280
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:36,537
or, uh, anything reflecting remorse.

281
00:16:36,621 --> 00:16:37,663
Um...

282
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:43,169
I left thinking this is a, um...

283
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:49,175
This is a person with no empathy.

284
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:52,512
[Frohnmayer] <i>Frankly, I'm convinced</i>
<i>the leadership of this group</i>

285
00:16:52,595 --> 00:16:54,305
<i>really believed they were above the law,</i>

286
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:56,432
<i>that they could move faster than our law</i>

287
00:16:56,516 --> 00:17:00,561
and that they could run circles around us
using our laws or breaking our laws.

288
00:17:00,645 --> 00:17:04,106
Uh... There was an arrogance about it
that's almost breathtaking.

289
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:07,401
[cameras clicking]

290
00:17:07,485 --> 00:17:11,989
Much of what happened is monstrous,

291
00:17:12,073 --> 00:17:17,828
and if Sheela had spent
the rest of her life in jail,

292
00:17:17,912 --> 00:17:20,665
that wouldn't have seemed
like an excessive sentence.

293
00:17:21,624 --> 00:17:23,543
[indistinct chatter]

294
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:26,003
[man]
No back-up?

295
00:17:26,087 --> 00:17:27,630
[man 2]
Okay, man, back-up.

296
00:17:31,676 --> 00:17:33,511
[Niren]
<i>So, he's in jail in Charlotte.</i>

297
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:39,475
<i>We were told he's going to go from</i>
<i>Charlotte on the next plane to Portland.</i>

298
00:17:40,810 --> 00:17:44,564
[male reporter] <i>Rajneesh's zigzag trip</i>
<i>back to Oregon began here Monday night</i>

299
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:46,816
<i>at the same airport</i>
<i>where he and six of his followers</i>

300
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,484
<i>were arrested October 28th.</i>

301
00:17:48,568 --> 00:17:51,112
<i>Bhagwan was put aboard</i>
<i>a U.S. Marshal's jet.</i>

302
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:54,240
[male reporter] <i>Rajneesh left Charlotte,</i>
<i>North Carolina yesterday afternoon</i>

303
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:58,160
<i>stopping in Missouri</i>
<i>before flying off to Oklahoma City.</i>

304
00:17:58,244 --> 00:18:00,496
[female reporter] <i>Apparently officials</i>
<i>now say he is spending another night</i>

305
00:18:00,580 --> 00:18:03,624
<i>in Oklahoma City</i>
<i>at an undisclosed location.</i>

306
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:06,043
[male reporter]
<i>He spent Tuesday and Wednesday nights</i>

307
00:18:06,127 --> 00:18:07,712
<i>at the El Reno Correction Institution.</i>

308
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:10,381
[female reporter]
<i>His third jail in just nine days.</i>

309
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:12,925
[female reporter]
<i>Where next for Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh?</i>

310
00:18:13,009 --> 00:18:14,343
[male reporter]
<i>As you said all week long,</i>

311
00:18:14,427 --> 00:18:15,970
<i>It's been something</i>
<i>of a cat and mouse game</i>

312
00:18:16,053 --> 00:18:17,388
<i>between federal marshals and reporters</i>

313
00:18:17,471 --> 00:18:19,390
as the U.S. Marshals
have been deliberately vague

314
00:18:19,473 --> 00:18:21,684
about the exact time
and place of his arrival.

315
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:24,395
They take as long as legally possible

316
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:27,982
taking him from facility to facility,
bussing him around.

317
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:34,280
What it gave them the opportunity to do is
drag him around the country for two weeks.

318
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:36,407
I think it's a tragedy for this country...

319
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:41,120
that this innocent and beautiful man...

320
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:45,499
is being held in this country's prisons.

321
00:18:46,042 --> 00:18:50,338
You know, this country is not
that far from the Wild West, right?

322
00:18:51,756 --> 00:18:54,675
<i>So they use every tool they have</i>

323
00:18:54,759 --> 00:18:59,930
to try and coerce accused to give up.

324
00:19:00,806 --> 00:19:02,058
[camera clicking]

325
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:06,354
<i>They often refuse voluntary surrender</i>
<i>so they can get their perp walk.</i>

326
00:19:07,355 --> 00:19:11,233
They like to arrest
and then put the person in the cuffs

327
00:19:11,317 --> 00:19:16,530
and make them walk through this barrage
of lights to make them look guilty.

328
00:19:16,614 --> 00:19:19,659
[man] <i>Well, to see a man</i>
<i>who's never hurt anyone</i>

329
00:19:19,742 --> 00:19:22,745
shackled like a psychopathic killer...

330
00:19:23,788 --> 00:19:27,166
shows me that the United States government
is terrified of this man.

331
00:19:27,249 --> 00:19:29,293
[male reporter]
<i>They persist in their belief that Bhagwan</i>

332
00:19:29,377 --> 00:19:32,380
<i>is being wrongly treated</i>
<i>and is becoming physically ill.</i>

333
00:19:32,463 --> 00:19:36,550
<i>Spokeswoman Prem Isabel called the case,</i>
<i>"government sponsored kidnapping."</i>

334
00:19:36,634 --> 00:19:38,469
All I'm concerned
is with Bhagwan's health.

335
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:40,680
I don't want the man to die in jail.

336
00:19:40,763 --> 00:19:45,643
That anyone could treat a man with
such grace and such beauty in that way,

337
00:19:45,726 --> 00:19:47,478
I just don't understand it.

338
00:19:47,561 --> 00:19:51,816
Uh... He is by no means being given
any special consideration

339
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:54,235
or any red carpet treatment so to speak.

340
00:19:54,318 --> 00:19:57,571
I think our assumption was he probably
wouldn't like that bus ride.

341
00:19:58,572 --> 00:20:00,825
<i>He probably wouldn't like his roommates.</i>

342
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:04,203
[Niren] <i>He was subsequently put</i>
<i>in a cell with an individual</i>

343
00:20:04,286 --> 00:20:07,164
who was diagnosed
as having contagious herpes.

344
00:20:07,248 --> 00:20:08,416
Herpes.

345
00:20:08,499 --> 00:20:10,835
I think this is outrageous.

346
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:12,169
[male reporter]
<i>Charges of mistreatment.</i>

347
00:20:12,253 --> 00:20:16,257
<i>Three strip searches allegedly performed</i>
<i>by local corrections officers.</i>

348
00:20:16,340 --> 00:20:17,675
[male reporter]
<i>At 6:30 this morning,</i>

349
00:20:17,758 --> 00:20:19,760
<i>Bhagwan was put back</i>
<i>on the Marshal's plane.</i>

350
00:20:20,469 --> 00:20:23,139
[male reporter] <i>From Tucson,</i>
<i>it was onto Vandenberg Air Force Base.</i>

351
00:20:23,764 --> 00:20:26,392
<i>From there,</i>
<i>it was a mid-afternoon stop in Sacramento.</i>

352
00:20:26,475 --> 00:20:29,520
Each time that they told him
that he was going to go somewhere,

353
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:32,690
<i>they told him</i>
<i>that he was going to Portland.</i>

354
00:20:32,773 --> 00:20:35,109
<i>And each time,</i>
<i>it turned out not to be true.</i>

355
00:20:35,192 --> 00:20:37,653
Richard, I understand
the U.S. Marshal is telling us

356
00:20:37,737 --> 00:20:40,489
that the plane has now landed
at Boeing Field in Seattle.

357
00:20:40,573 --> 00:20:42,158
<i>That happened just a few minutes ago.</i>

358
00:20:42,241 --> 00:20:44,910
<i>Our information is</i>
<i>that Bhagwan will be transferred</i>

359
00:20:44,994 --> 00:20:47,288
<i>from that bigger airplane to a smaller one</i>

360
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:50,040
<i>which will in fact bring him here</i>
<i>to the Portland air base.</i>

361
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:53,419
[Weaver] <i>Between the time</i>
<i>that he was arrested in Charlotte</i>

362
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:55,087
<i>and he got back to Portland,</i>

363
00:20:55,171 --> 00:20:57,673
I think it was almost three weeks.

364
00:21:00,426 --> 00:21:02,970
<i>And as a result of that environment...</i>

365
00:21:04,013 --> 00:21:05,681
he was ready to surrender.

366
00:21:13,063 --> 00:21:15,566
[male reporter] <i>Sheela,</i>
<i>Bhagwan's former personal secretary,</i>

367
00:21:15,649 --> 00:21:18,402
<i>back in Oregon</i>
<i>to face charges of attempted murder,</i>

368
00:21:18,486 --> 00:21:21,113
<i>first degree assault</i>
<i>and conspiracy to commit murder.</i>

369
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:25,951
[male reporter] <i>This time there was</i>
<i>no entourage of Rajneeshee supporters.</i>

370
00:21:26,035 --> 00:21:29,663
<i>Sheela came to the U.S. Courthouse</i>
<i>in Portland under heavy guard,</i>

371
00:21:29,747 --> 00:21:32,124
<i>virtually surrounded by federal marshals.</i>

372
00:21:33,417 --> 00:21:34,835
[male reporter]
<i>State authorities say</i>

373
00:21:34,919 --> 00:21:37,171
<i>she tried to poison</i>
<i>two Wasco County commissioners</i>

374
00:21:37,254 --> 00:21:40,132
<i>and tried to burn</i>
<i>down the Wasco County Planning Office.</i>

375
00:21:40,216 --> 00:21:42,676
<i>I thought if Sheela did all of this,</i>

376
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:47,973
it would be possible
for her to testify against Osho...

377
00:21:48,724 --> 00:21:51,060
avoid prosecution herself...

378
00:21:52,937 --> 00:21:56,607
and that Osho could be subject
to criminal prosecution.

379
00:21:56,690 --> 00:21:58,776
[camera clicking]

380
00:21:58,859 --> 00:22:04,657
[Sheela] <i>It was never a thought</i>
<i>in my mind to barter against Bhagwan</i>

381
00:22:04,740 --> 00:22:06,659
<i>or barter with anybody</i>

382
00:22:06,742 --> 00:22:11,914
so that... I can avoid my misery.

383
00:22:13,123 --> 00:22:19,088
You cannot betray people
for their own freedom.

384
00:22:19,171 --> 00:22:20,798
[male reporter]
<i>And some major developments tonight.</i>

385
00:22:20,881 --> 00:22:25,344
Ma Anand Sheela appeared
in federal court today to plead guilty.

386
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:27,721
[female reporter] <i>Sheela arrived</i>
<i>this morning to plead guilty</i>

387
00:22:27,805 --> 00:22:31,392
<i>to charges ranging</i>
<i>from mass poisonings to wiretappings.</i>

388
00:22:32,935 --> 00:22:35,563
<i>Sheela will serve the</i>
<i>four-and-one-half-year prison sentence,</i>

389
00:22:35,646 --> 00:22:38,857
<i>pay fines totaling $469,000</i>

390
00:22:38,941 --> 00:22:41,610
<i>and agree to leave the U.S.</i>
<i>after she is released.</i>

391
00:22:47,866 --> 00:22:50,244
<i>Ma Shanti Bhadra,</i>
<i>another former commune leader,</i>

392
00:22:50,327 --> 00:22:52,746
<i>pleaded guilty</i>
<i>to attempted murder of the doctor.</i>

393
00:22:52,830 --> 00:22:54,832
<i>She'll serve ten years in prison.</i>

394
00:22:57,376 --> 00:22:58,669
[Jane]
<i>It was decided</i>

395
00:22:58,752 --> 00:23:03,632
<i>that Sheela and I would serve</i>
<i>our sentences in a federal prison.</i>

396
00:23:03,716 --> 00:23:08,679
The authorities felt it was better
for my safety not to be in Oregon.

397
00:23:09,430 --> 00:23:12,349
<i>And so I, too, was sent</i>
<i>to the federal prison.</i>

398
00:23:13,517 --> 00:23:15,644
<i>It didn't get any better, I'm afraid.</i>

399
00:23:16,270 --> 00:23:21,066
I truly believed
that I'd been locked into a mental asylum.

400
00:23:21,150 --> 00:23:25,738
People were screaming,
banging on the tin doors.

401
00:23:26,405 --> 00:23:27,990
<i>It was pandemonium.</i>

402
00:23:30,659 --> 00:23:36,206
<i>Through all of that, my son Peter</i>
<i>still lived in Rajneeshpuram.</i>

403
00:23:36,290 --> 00:23:39,960
<i>And when I was in prison,</i>
<i>Peter came to visit me.</i>

404
00:23:41,003 --> 00:23:43,088
That changed me.

405
00:23:44,089 --> 00:23:46,800
Because of all that had happened
around Rajneeshpuram,

406
00:23:46,884 --> 00:23:50,638
because of Bhagwan's attacks,
Peter asked me what had happened.

407
00:23:52,056 --> 00:23:56,393
<i>The abandonment,</i>
<i>it was just awful for him...</i>

408
00:23:57,519 --> 00:24:02,441
and very painful for me
to sit behind glass,

409
00:24:02,524 --> 00:24:07,988
to see the confusion
and the pain in my son's eyes.

410
00:24:08,864 --> 00:24:13,243
<i>That was</i>
<i>when the first seed began to stir,</i>

411
00:24:13,327 --> 00:24:16,664
<i>the seed</i>
<i>that would take me away from Bhagwan.</i>

412
00:24:16,747 --> 00:24:21,418
It was the beginning
of a very long journey...

413
00:24:22,795 --> 00:24:25,047
of breaking the spell.

414
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:27,758
Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh
will get his day in court.

415
00:24:27,841 --> 00:24:30,552
Richard Draper listened
as the lawyers argued over trial dates

416
00:24:30,636 --> 00:24:33,263
in the Rajneesh case,
now before a federal judge.

417
00:24:33,347 --> 00:24:36,183
And, Richard, was today's hearing
a preview of things to come?

418
00:24:36,266 --> 00:24:37,559
Oh, very much so, Mark.

419
00:24:37,643 --> 00:24:41,980
<i>Legally, it promises to be</i>
<i>a tangled web made for lawyers.</i>

420
00:24:43,273 --> 00:24:46,276
[Niren]
<i>After Osho got back to Portland...</i>

