642
00:39:37,208 --> 00:39:40,253
<i>made the pilgrimage to observe</i>
<i>the new government take office.</i>

643
00:39:40,336 --> 00:39:44,132
[all] And I will support the constitution
of the United States of America.

644
00:39:44,215 --> 00:39:48,177
[man] Several years ago,
we would never have dreamed

645
00:39:48,261 --> 00:39:53,808
that anything could happen
to a little community such as this.

646
00:39:54,434 --> 00:39:56,269
But we can't live in the past.

647
00:39:58,021 --> 00:40:02,483
[Bowerman] <i>Well, this whole thing</i>
<i>that we endured with the Rajneeshees,</i>

648
00:40:02,567 --> 00:40:06,446
it's-- It's similar
to a football or basketball game.

649
00:40:10,325 --> 00:40:12,744
<i>Somebody's going to lose,</i>
<i>somebody is going to win.</i>

650
00:40:13,703 --> 00:40:17,582
When it's all over and done with,
uh, the season's over...

651
00:40:17,665 --> 00:40:18,583
[clears throat]

652
00:40:18,666 --> 00:40:20,126
the champion is crowned.

653
00:40:22,211 --> 00:40:23,880
Of course we won.

654
00:40:25,048 --> 00:40:26,966
<i>Just outside the post office</i>

655
00:40:27,050 --> 00:40:32,263
is a flag pole
and a little statue of an antelope.

656
00:40:32,347 --> 00:40:34,724
<i>It was donated to the community</i>

657
00:40:34,807 --> 00:40:39,020
for standing up
under this pressure that we endured.

658
00:40:42,857 --> 00:40:45,068
[male reporter]
<i>The quotation from Edmund Burke,</i>

659
00:40:45,151 --> 00:40:50,365
<i>"The only thing necessary for the triumph</i>
<i>of evil is for good men to do nothing."</i>

660
00:40:50,448 --> 00:40:52,867
[Kelly]
<i>It will serve as a constant reminder</i>

661
00:40:52,951 --> 00:40:57,288
that now that we have Antelope back,
we should remember that we almost lost it.

662
00:40:58,957 --> 00:41:03,461
And I look forward to the day
that I don't remember the Rajneesh at all

663
00:41:03,544 --> 00:41:05,088
until I come in and see that flagpole.

664
00:41:06,089 --> 00:41:10,343
[Bowerman] <i>For me,</i>
<i>you miss some of the excitement.</i>

665
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:14,055
For some reason, I don't know why,

666
00:41:14,138 --> 00:41:18,184
but I sure love the fight! [chuckles]

667
00:41:19,602 --> 00:41:22,313
[Silvertooth]
<i>Antelope, it was never the same.</i>

668
00:41:23,356 --> 00:41:26,275
Well, you know so many people had left

669
00:41:26,359 --> 00:41:29,779
that you weren't going back
to what you were before.

670
00:41:29,862 --> 00:41:31,990
It's just not together anymore.

671
00:41:32,073 --> 00:41:35,368
Not a little community like it was.

672
00:41:36,869 --> 00:41:38,204
[Silvertooth]
<i>Cafe and the store are closed.</i>

673
00:41:39,789 --> 00:41:43,292
<i>You know, there was a school here</i>
<i>until all that brouhaha.</i>

674
00:41:44,085 --> 00:41:46,879
<i>You know, time marches on.</i>

675
00:41:47,755 --> 00:41:52,218
It was an extremely unpleasant
part of my life.

676
00:41:52,301 --> 00:41:57,515
And I just would like it to be over with
and not to have to talk about it anymore.

677
00:41:57,598 --> 00:41:59,684
And I don't want for people to meet me

678
00:41:59,767 --> 00:42:03,730
and say, "Oh, yes, I remember your name,"
or "Oh, were you involved with them?"

679
00:42:03,813 --> 00:42:07,400
I don't think
that they're worth that, either.

680
00:42:10,528 --> 00:42:11,404
No.

681
00:42:15,867 --> 00:42:17,285
[male reporter]
<i>This is your first interview.</i>

682
00:42:17,368 --> 00:42:20,997
<i>Your chance</i>
<i>to say something to Oregonians.</i>

683
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:22,540
Now are you daring me?

684
00:42:22,623 --> 00:42:24,250
[male reporter]
I'm daring you to look at the camera--

685
00:42:24,333 --> 00:42:26,252
Are you daring me to do this?

686
00:42:26,335 --> 00:42:28,296
I'm just asking, you know,
after a year down here,

687
00:42:28,379 --> 00:42:31,299
looking back on all of what happened,
looking back on all of that.

688
00:42:32,008 --> 00:42:36,512
- Today, looking back on that experience.
- Okay. I say to all Oregonians...

689
00:42:37,638 --> 00:42:40,016
that you did not understand Bhagwan,

690
00:42:40,099 --> 00:42:43,561
nor did you understand his teaching,
nor did you understand Sheela.

691
00:42:43,644 --> 00:42:48,983
You have missed out on Rajneeshee,
their business, their intelligence...

692
00:42:49,067 --> 00:42:55,782
and their very special ability
of celebration and laughter.

693
00:42:56,866 --> 00:43:01,454
I laugh more at you

694
00:43:01,537 --> 00:43:06,751
than Oregonians who say that we are happy
that Sheela is in prison.

695
00:43:06,834 --> 00:43:07,835
No.

696
00:43:10,213 --> 00:43:12,924
Are you sorry about anything
that happened in Oregon,

697
00:43:13,007 --> 00:43:14,300
the people that did get sick,

698
00:43:14,383 --> 00:43:17,178
the people that did get hurt
by all of this? Do you have any remorse?

699
00:43:17,261 --> 00:43:20,431
People get sick
all over the world on daily basis.

700
00:43:20,515 --> 00:43:22,058
Why should I feel remorse?

701
00:43:22,892 --> 00:43:27,188
I feel bad that Oregonian
made the same mistake.

702
00:43:27,271 --> 00:43:33,694
They made it in treating blacks,
American Indians, Mormons, Catholics

703
00:43:33,778 --> 00:43:36,864
and any other minorities
they have treated up till now.

704
00:43:36,948 --> 00:43:38,491
That I felt bad for.

705
00:43:39,242 --> 00:43:41,869
But, hey,
I never claimed to change humanity.

706
00:43:41,953 --> 00:43:43,204
I still don't.

707
00:43:45,414 --> 00:43:48,876
[Sheela] <i>I don't have</i>
<i>much to say about my time in prison.</i>

708
00:43:52,296 --> 00:43:56,217
Bear in mind, I have paid full penalty...

709
00:43:57,677 --> 00:44:03,141
what was charged
to me under American legal system.

710
00:44:05,977 --> 00:44:10,690
In Switzerland, in Europe,
people are not considered criminal

711
00:44:10,773 --> 00:44:15,862
once they have paid
their dues and are crime-free.

712
00:44:18,156 --> 00:44:19,615
[chanting]

713
00:44:22,994 --> 00:44:26,164
[female reporter] <i>Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh</i>
<i>announced he planned to live in India.</i>

714
00:44:26,747 --> 00:44:28,541
[male reporter] <i>Reception yesterday</i>
<i>at the New Delhi airport</i>

715
00:44:28,624 --> 00:44:30,918
<i>indicates Bhagwan</i>
<i>still has followers in India.</i>

716
00:44:31,002 --> 00:44:34,714
<i>Bhagwan told his followers, "If they</i>
<i>can harass me, they can harass you."</i>

717
00:44:34,797 --> 00:44:39,093
<i>Bhagwan called Rajneeshpuram</i>
<i>a beautiful experiment that failed.</i>

718
00:44:41,053 --> 00:44:42,471
He ended up back in India.

719
00:45:04,869 --> 00:45:09,540
And after he got back to Poona, then
people started going back to India again.

720
00:45:12,501 --> 00:45:16,130
<i>So I went to India</i>
<i>because I still wanted to be around him</i>

721
00:45:16,213 --> 00:45:18,633
<i>and it was still a great place to be.</i>

722
00:45:23,137 --> 00:45:25,640
<i>At some point he said, "I'm not him.</i>

723
00:45:26,515 --> 00:45:29,602
<i>I'm not this Bhagwan person.</i>
<i>I'm not anybody."</i>

724
00:45:30,645 --> 00:45:34,482
And then people wrote to him and said,
"We got to call you something!"

725
00:45:34,565 --> 00:45:36,108
[chuckles]
You know, "Prince?"

726
00:45:39,528 --> 00:45:42,531
<i>And one of the suggestions</i>
<i>was the name "Osho."</i>

727
00:45:43,574 --> 00:45:45,576
<i>Osho is from the Japanese.</i>

728
00:45:45,660 --> 00:45:47,036
<i>It's an honorarium.</i>

729
00:45:48,204 --> 00:45:52,833
<i>You would speak to your teacher,</i>
<i>your master as Osho.</i>

730
00:45:58,506 --> 00:46:01,759
<i>He'd always been frail,</i>

731
00:46:01,842 --> 00:46:06,305
but he was like almost transparent,
his skin, you know?

732
00:46:07,556 --> 00:46:09,225
Almost like he wasn't there.

733
00:46:13,104 --> 00:46:14,772
<i>He stopped speaking again.</i>

734
00:46:15,147 --> 00:46:16,983
<i>So he was no longer giving discourses.</i>

735
00:46:17,066 --> 00:46:18,526
<i>He would come out...</i>

736
00:46:20,277 --> 00:46:21,362
<i>greet people...</i>

737
00:46:26,659 --> 00:46:28,285
<i>and he would move across the podium</i>

738
00:46:28,369 --> 00:46:33,165
while staying facing forward
to the people there, blessing them.

739
00:46:46,762 --> 00:46:49,557
<i>And that time</i>
<i>I was sitting about three rows back</i>

740
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:52,810
and he was wavering a little bit.

741
00:46:54,270 --> 00:47:00,484
And at one time I could actually see
his toe was over the edge of the podium.

742
00:47:02,486 --> 00:47:06,991
And I was just willing him to stay alive,

743
00:47:07,074 --> 00:47:13,414
trying to give my life energy to him.

744
00:47:16,709 --> 00:47:19,211
[crowd shouts]
Osho!

745
00:47:19,295 --> 00:47:21,297
And the next day...

746
00:47:22,048 --> 00:47:26,469
<i>everybody was called together</i>
<i>into the Buddha Hall.</i>

747
00:47:34,852 --> 00:47:38,856
[Deva Raj] Yesterday morning, I noticed
that Osho was obviously leaving his body.

748
00:47:39,523 --> 00:47:43,277
We sat on the bed
and he gave us his final words.

749
00:47:46,447 --> 00:47:49,617
He said, "I leave you my dream."

750
00:47:54,205 --> 00:47:59,460
He then lay back quietly and we sat
with him while I held his pulse.

751
00:48:04,423 --> 00:48:05,925
Slowly it faded.

752
00:48:09,762 --> 00:48:13,599
When I could hardly feel it,
I said to him, "Osho, I think this is it."

753
00:48:14,642 --> 00:48:18,145
He just nodded gently
and closed his eyes for the last time.

754
00:48:45,714 --> 00:48:50,886
His body was brought
into the... Buddha Hall...

755
00:49:00,646 --> 00:49:02,731
and placed up on the podium.

756
00:49:08,737 --> 00:49:11,991
[all shout]
Osho!

757
00:49:22,543 --> 00:49:25,629
There are many other things
that he said that we'll let you know,

758
00:49:25,713 --> 00:49:27,590
but for now let me just say to you

759
00:49:27,673 --> 00:49:31,385
that, in death, he was just as you
would have expected, incredible.

760
00:49:32,178 --> 00:49:34,930
[cheering and applause]

761
00:49:49,778 --> 00:49:55,242
And then it was taken from there
to the burning ghats.

762
00:49:55,326 --> 00:50:00,956
Huge procession
with people carrying his body.

763
00:50:19,391 --> 00:50:22,228
[rhythmic clapping and chanting]

764
00:50:23,520 --> 00:50:28,943
And I was standing there,
uh... watching his body burn.

765
00:50:41,413 --> 00:50:45,251
Such a gift... [voice breaks] he was.

766
00:50:48,504 --> 00:50:49,838
Such a gift.

767
00:50:55,135 --> 00:50:56,804
[cheering]

768
00:51:05,187 --> 00:51:07,481
[chanting]

769
00:51:22,037 --> 00:51:26,083
[Jane] <i>When I heard that Bhagwan,</i>
<i>now known as Osho, had died...</i>

770
00:51:28,669 --> 00:51:30,754
<i>I was strangely indifferent.</i>

771
00:51:31,714 --> 00:51:34,925
<i>That was something behind me.</i>

772
00:51:37,469 --> 00:51:41,056
I'd been in prison
and now I was coming home.

773
00:51:42,057 --> 00:51:45,769
I was 43 years old, but I was a child.

774
00:51:47,229 --> 00:51:49,940
My parents opened their arms to me...

775
00:51:51,525 --> 00:51:53,319
just held me...

776
00:51:54,320 --> 00:51:55,696
<i>and took me home with them.</i>

777
00:51:56,905 --> 00:51:58,615
<i>Not very long after,</i>

778
00:51:58,699 --> 00:52:03,412
<i>I started running a juice bar</i>
<i>in Germany called the Saftladen.</i>

779
00:52:04,705 --> 00:52:07,333
<i>I met my husband George in this juice bar.</i>

780
00:52:09,585 --> 00:52:13,756
And slowly, slowly I began
to get back to planet Earth.

781
00:52:20,679 --> 00:52:24,058
<i>At the same time, outside Germany,</i>

782
00:52:24,141 --> 00:52:28,896
<i>there was still an international</i>
<i>arrest warrant hanging over my head.</i>

783
00:52:28,979 --> 00:52:34,568
<i>The case to murder</i>
<i>Mr. Turner remained open.</i>

784
00:52:36,070 --> 00:52:37,863
[female reporter]
<i>The prosecution alleged that the women</i>

785
00:52:37,946 --> 00:52:41,116
<i>plotted to kill Oregon's</i>
<i>former U.S. Attorney, Charles Turner.</i>

786
00:52:42,117 --> 00:52:46,455
<i>If found guilty, the women could be given</i>
<i>a life sentence in a U.S. jail.</i>

787
00:52:47,498 --> 00:52:50,000
[Jane]
<i>But also at that time,</i>

788
00:52:50,084 --> 00:52:53,295
<i>I had a stability I had never had before.</i>

789
00:52:53,379 --> 00:52:59,551
<i>I was free from prosecution in America</i>
<i>as long as I could stay in Germany.</i>

790
00:53:01,261 --> 00:53:02,262
<i>And one day...</i>

791
00:53:03,847 --> 00:53:06,850
<i>in the middle of the night,</i>
<i>the phone rang.</i>

792
00:53:07,559 --> 00:53:09,478
It was my daughter-in-law.

793
00:53:09,561 --> 00:53:13,107
"Jane," she said. "Peter is in hospital."

794
00:53:15,943 --> 00:53:19,363
I was hearing for the first time
that my son had a brain tumor...

795
00:53:20,114 --> 00:53:21,907
and that he might die.

796
00:53:22,408 --> 00:53:24,493
<i>I was in absolute shock.</i>

797
00:53:25,661 --> 00:53:32,501
But the arrest warrant meant I could not
travel to Australia to go to my dying son.

798
00:53:33,710 --> 00:53:35,504
I had to travel to America.

799
00:53:35,587 --> 00:53:38,090
I had to throw myself
at the mercy of the court

800
00:53:38,173 --> 00:53:41,427
without any guarantees whatsoever.

801
00:53:41,510 --> 00:53:46,640
I wanted to be free to be able to go
to my children at a time like this.

802
00:53:48,475 --> 00:53:50,769
<i>George and I went</i>
<i>to the airport in Frankfurt</i>

803
00:53:50,853 --> 00:53:52,938
<i>and boarded a plane for Portland.</i>

804
00:53:55,149 --> 00:53:58,152
<i>We walked together</i>
<i>to the federal courthouse.</i>

805
00:53:58,235 --> 00:53:59,862
<i>It was raining that morning.</i>

806
00:54:00,779 --> 00:54:03,282
I was very, very focused.

807
00:54:04,158 --> 00:54:09,580
The court had the discretion
of sentencing me to life imprisonment,

808
00:54:09,663 --> 00:54:15,210
but I knew that this was
what had to be done.

809
00:54:16,545 --> 00:54:18,547
<i>As proceedings began,</i>

810
00:54:18,630 --> 00:54:20,507
<i>first the prosecutor spoke</i>

811
00:54:20,591 --> 00:54:25,220
and asked that the judge
sentence me appropriately.

812
00:54:25,304 --> 00:54:27,055
Then it was my turn to speak.

813
00:54:27,723 --> 00:54:31,602
I felt compelled to stand
to what I had done.

814
00:54:33,103 --> 00:54:34,646
<i>I read my statement.</i>

815
00:54:36,064 --> 00:54:40,611
<i>And then the moment</i>
<i>had come for sentencing.</i>

816
00:54:43,363 --> 00:54:49,328
Judge Marsh said that sometimes justice
is stronger than mercy

817
00:54:49,411 --> 00:54:50,871
and that's okay.

818
00:54:51,955 --> 00:54:57,503
But sometimes mercy overrules justice.

819
00:54:59,087 --> 00:55:01,798
And we have such a case before us today.

820
00:55:03,592 --> 00:55:08,597
And therefore,
he was sentencing me to time served.

821
00:55:13,227 --> 00:55:14,228
I was free.

822
00:55:15,938 --> 00:55:17,856
I was free.

823
00:55:19,274 --> 00:55:20,234
And through my tears,

824
00:55:20,317 --> 00:55:24,863
I could see that everybody
in the courtroom was happy for me.

825
00:55:25,364 --> 00:55:29,826
FBI agents came up to me, shook my hand,

826
00:55:29,910 --> 00:55:35,249
and said "Congratulations, Mrs. Stork.
You deserve it."

827
00:55:35,874 --> 00:55:38,043
I wasn't a criminal in that moment.

828
00:55:39,670 --> 00:55:45,133
I was a free woman
with a son who was dying...

829
00:55:46,051 --> 00:55:48,887
and that brought everybody together...

830
00:55:50,347 --> 00:55:53,058
in a very human way.

831
00:55:55,686 --> 00:55:57,771
Even today when I think about it...

832
00:56:00,440 --> 00:56:02,526
Yeah, it brings tears to my eyes.

833
00:56:03,694 --> 00:56:07,614
It was the most incredible experience

834
00:56:07,698 --> 00:56:12,327
to become aware that they were
a lot of people around me that day

835
00:56:12,411 --> 00:56:18,208
who were glad that I could go to my son
and be with him when he died.

836
00:56:30,178 --> 00:56:34,224
[Sheela] <i>After prison,</i>
<i>I had to get back on my feet.</i>

837
00:56:37,352 --> 00:56:40,814
<i>I had to find way to survive.</i>

838
00:56:43,734 --> 00:56:49,114
<i>When I left Bhagwan,</i>
<i>I left the Sannyasin community also.</i>

839
00:56:51,450 --> 00:56:53,243
<i>I left hypocrisy.</i>

840
00:56:55,704 --> 00:57:02,502
<i>It is time that Bhagwan's Sannyasins</i>
<i>open their eyes...</i>

841
00:57:03,587 --> 00:57:09,176
and look at the reality
of what had happened to Bhagwan.

842
00:57:09,259 --> 00:57:11,720
Bhagwan didn't have a natural death.

843
00:57:13,972 --> 00:57:17,309
<i>This doctor,</i>
<i>who had written death certificate...</i>

844
00:57:19,186 --> 00:57:22,147
felt it was with overdose.

845
00:57:27,235 --> 00:57:31,698
[Deva Raj] <i>About nine months ago,</i>
<i>Osho formed the inner circle...</i>

846
00:57:32,240 --> 00:57:34,743
<i>a group of Sannyasins now numbering 20.</i>

847
00:57:34,826 --> 00:57:37,204
<i>The inner circle would be his successor.</i>

848
00:57:39,039 --> 00:57:42,042
[Sheela] <i>These are the same people</i>
<i>who were drugging him...</i>

849
00:57:43,835 --> 00:57:49,091
and the same people
who are looting him for his riches.

850
00:57:52,344 --> 00:57:56,431
<i>It was your responsibility</i>
<i>to take care of Bhagwan.</i>

851
00:57:56,515 --> 00:58:01,061
At least in my time, he was safe.

852
00:58:03,230 --> 00:58:08,860
<i>But Sannyasin community is my past.</i>

853
00:58:10,696 --> 00:58:17,369
In spite of what world thinks,
I have come out with upper hand.

854
00:58:24,126 --> 00:58:28,588
I work with schizophrenia to dements,

855
00:58:28,672 --> 00:58:31,216
from Parkinson's to Alzheimer,

856
00:58:31,299 --> 00:58:34,428
and young and old dements.

857
00:58:35,971 --> 00:58:38,932
<i>I didn't want old people rejected.</i>

858
00:58:41,810 --> 00:58:44,312
<i>What have I learned from Bhagwan?</i>

859
00:58:47,107 --> 00:58:52,404
<i>How can I implement</i>
<i>his teachings in my daily life?</i>

860
00:58:55,073 --> 00:58:56,867
<i>This commune...</i>

861
00:58:56,950 --> 00:59:00,370
<i>This is what I have learned from Bhagwan.</i>

862
00:59:02,622 --> 00:59:04,041
<i>We eat together.</i>

863
00:59:05,542 --> 00:59:08,211
<i>We sing, dance...</i>

864
00:59:10,839 --> 00:59:14,092
<i>sleep in this house in comfort together.</i>

865
00:59:14,885 --> 00:59:20,640
They can become old in my house
and remain till the last moment.

866
00:59:27,189 --> 00:59:29,858
<i>It is a wonderful way...</i>

867
00:59:30,901 --> 00:59:34,738
of saying thank you to existence.

868
00:59:37,074 --> 00:59:39,409
[Jayananda]
<i>We, as Sannyasins,</i>

869
00:59:39,493 --> 00:59:43,705
should light the consciousness
of people around the world.

870
00:59:44,998 --> 00:59:50,295
<i>You could see</i>
<i>Osho's vision come to fruition.</i>

871
00:59:52,297 --> 00:59:53,131
[screams]

872
00:59:56,426 --> 01:00:00,263
<i>There are still communities</i>
<i>devoted to him and his teachings.</i>

873
01:00:01,515 --> 01:00:02,891
<i>South America...</i>

874
01:00:04,309 --> 01:00:05,143
<i>Europe...</i>

875
01:00:05,685 --> 01:00:06,895
<i>and Asia.</i>

876
01:00:08,688 --> 01:00:12,859
<i>His publishing</i>
<i>is growing dramatically now.</i>

877
01:00:12,943 --> 01:00:15,445
<i>It's published in like 50 languages.</i>

878
01:00:16,488 --> 01:00:19,825
<i>Like 1,000 new book contracts</i>
<i>in the last year.</i>

879
01:00:21,743 --> 01:00:25,413
[Sunshine] <i>There are young people</i>
<i>flocking to Poona today...</i>

880
01:00:26,164 --> 01:00:28,917
<i>to go and learn about his meditations...</i>

881
01:00:29,668 --> 01:00:31,461
<i>and dance in Buddha Hall.</i>

882
01:00:33,922 --> 01:00:38,009
[woman] <i>There is a full day program</i>
<i>of meditations available here,</i>

883
01:00:38,093 --> 01:00:41,930
<i>all day, every day,</i>
<i>from morning till night.</i>

884
01:00:43,306 --> 01:00:49,396
So, his work, his teachings will live on.

885
01:00:52,607 --> 01:00:55,443
[Silvertooth]
<i>It all smells like a gimmick to me.</i>

886
01:00:56,903 --> 01:01:00,031
<i>You know, I just think</i>
<i>it's a fleece from day one.</i>

887
01:01:01,867 --> 01:01:03,660
<i>I thought he was an old con man.</i>

888
01:01:05,078 --> 01:01:06,830
<i>They were sitting there in India</i>

889
01:01:06,913 --> 01:01:10,041
<i>and they saw</i>
<i>all these rich young Europeans</i>

890
01:01:10,125 --> 01:01:13,378
tripping around, looking for God.

891
01:01:15,130 --> 01:01:18,717
And they figured out these people
have got a lot of money,

892
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:22,804
so they set up shop and created Bhagwan...

893
01:01:23,847 --> 01:01:27,642
<i>and found out</i>
<i>that it was pretty easy to fleece them.</i>

894
01:01:27,726 --> 01:01:29,728
People want to believe.
They want to belong.

895
01:01:29,811 --> 01:01:31,354
They want to think, you know,

896
01:01:31,438 --> 01:01:35,358
me having sex all day long is going
to really send me to heaven.

897
01:01:38,028 --> 01:01:40,030
[laughs]

898
01:01:41,031 --> 01:01:42,616
<i>Anyway, that's my opinion.</i>

899
01:01:43,200 --> 01:01:46,745
<i>After the Rajneeshees left,</i>
<i>this guy Dennis Washington--</i>

900
01:01:46,828 --> 01:01:50,790
<i>He's a billionaire developer from Montana.</i>

901
01:01:51,333 --> 01:01:55,754
He bought the ranch and he ended up
gifting the thing to Young Life.

902
01:01:56,838 --> 01:01:59,299
It's a Christian youth organization.

903
01:01:59,382 --> 01:02:02,260
They call them camps.
It's more like a resort to me.

904
01:02:18,818 --> 01:02:23,740
We went from free sex, the Rajneeshees,
to no sex, Young Life.

905
01:02:23,823 --> 01:02:28,453
They're very much abstinence-oriented
for their young people.

906
01:02:28,536 --> 01:02:30,372
<i>It's kind of like a cult too.</i>

907
01:02:30,455 --> 01:02:32,290
<i>They're not perfect.</i>

908
01:02:32,374 --> 01:02:34,918
But they're much better neighbors
than the Rajneeshees.

909
01:02:35,001 --> 01:02:36,461
[laughs]

910
01:02:36,544 --> 01:02:38,713
They're not waving AK-47's in your face.

911
01:02:42,259 --> 01:02:43,969
[Niren]
<i>They trade on people's fear.</i>

912
01:02:44,844 --> 01:02:50,350
<i>And they do that by defining a group</i>
<i>that they can fear and hate.</i>

913
01:02:51,643 --> 01:02:56,106
<i>And then they totally misrepresent</i>
<i>who you are.</i>

914
01:02:57,857 --> 01:02:59,901
<i>I think the United States has failed.</i>

915
01:03:00,986 --> 01:03:04,990
The United States has failed to recognize
the most beautiful man I've ever seen.

916
01:03:06,199 --> 01:03:09,995
I think the United States has failed
to recognize the contribution

917
01:03:10,078 --> 01:03:12,998
that he had to offer
to this country and to the world.

918
01:03:13,081 --> 01:03:14,666
I think it's a tragedy.

919
01:03:17,043 --> 01:03:19,337
[Niren]
<i>From the legal political side of it,</i>

920
01:03:19,421 --> 01:03:24,926
I am the only one who really knows it in
the depth that it can be shared, you know?

921
01:03:29,389 --> 01:03:32,267
It is somewhat difficult and painful

922
01:03:32,350 --> 01:03:36,813
to talk about what happened to Osho
in the United States.

923
01:03:38,064 --> 01:03:41,026
Obviously I loved him very much

924
01:03:41,109 --> 01:03:43,403
and I was committed to the community.

925
01:03:46,239 --> 01:03:50,493
<i>And we were committed</i>
<i>to working really hard</i>

926
01:03:50,577 --> 01:03:57,250
<i>to manifest his vision</i>
<i>of the transformation of the planet.</i>

927
01:04:00,920 --> 01:04:02,130
Before he died...

928
01:04:03,631 --> 01:04:05,467
<i>I was told,</i>
<i>"Osho wants to talk to you."</i>

929
01:04:06,634 --> 01:04:08,053
So I went in...

930
01:04:09,137 --> 01:04:14,893
and he said, "Clear my name
in America by writing a book

931
01:04:14,976 --> 01:04:17,228
and telling the truth
about what happened."

932
01:04:19,272 --> 01:04:20,315
And...

933
01:04:24,319 --> 01:04:27,822
it's taken a long time
and it's had some twists and turns,

934
01:04:27,906 --> 01:04:32,369
but that's what I'm doing,
is finishing that book now.

935
01:04:32,452 --> 01:04:34,162
[Damien Jurado's "Cloudy Shoes" playing]

936
01:04:34,245 --> 01:04:35,830
<i>♪ I wish that</i>
<i>I wish that ♪</i>

937
01:04:35,914 --> 01:04:38,792
<i>♪ I could float</i>
<i>I could float ♪</i>

938
01:04:38,875 --> 01:04:42,504
<i>♪ Float up from the ground... ♪</i>

939
01:04:44,881 --> 01:04:47,926
So what I would say to people
is try to go on the journey.

940
01:04:50,470 --> 01:04:52,222
<i>The truth lies within.</i>

941
01:04:52,305 --> 01:04:55,266
<i>♪ What that's like... ♪</i>

942
01:04:58,269 --> 01:05:00,855
<i>He remains the master of masters.</i>

943
01:05:00,939 --> 01:05:03,942
<i>♪ About you</i>
<i>About you ♪</i>

944
01:05:04,025 --> 01:05:05,652
<i>♪ I wish... ♪</i>

945
01:05:05,735 --> 01:05:06,861
Start the journey.

946
01:05:08,780 --> 01:05:10,240
It'll change your life.

947
01:05:10,323 --> 01:05:13,201
<i>♪ I thought it was</i>
<i>I thought it was ♪</i>

948
01:05:13,284 --> 01:05:16,162
<i>♪ Impossible</i>
<i>Impossible ♪</i>

949
01:05:16,246 --> 01:05:19,499
<i>♪ To live and love like you... ♪</i>

950
01:05:19,582 --> 01:05:23,253
Bhagwan used to tell
stories of the Zen master

951
01:05:23,336 --> 01:05:30,051
who, seeing that his disciple
was ready for enlightenment,

952
01:05:31,177 --> 01:05:33,805
struck him with a stick and killed him.

953
01:05:34,472 --> 01:05:39,144
But in the moment before his death,
he became enlightened.

954
01:05:40,395 --> 01:05:43,731
And I ask myself again and again,

955
01:05:44,858 --> 01:05:47,068
"Did I miss the blow from the master?

956
01:05:47,152 --> 01:05:48,403
Did I run away...

957
01:05:49,821 --> 01:05:54,117
and not wait for that blow
that would bring me enlightenment?"

958
01:05:54,200 --> 01:06:01,040
It took me many, many years
before I was free of this suspicion...

959
01:06:02,625 --> 01:06:04,335
that I had somehow failed.

960
01:06:05,837 --> 01:06:11,217
As I'm saying this, I have
the picture of a grub in a cocoon.

961
01:06:12,010 --> 01:06:15,346
<i>If you've ever watched</i>
<i>a butterfly come out of its cocoon,</i>

962
01:06:15,430 --> 01:06:17,390
<i>it's a long difficult process,</i>

963
01:06:18,266 --> 01:06:19,893
squeezing and moving

964
01:06:19,976 --> 01:06:26,900
and the cocoon
is clinging to the moth's body

965
01:06:26,983 --> 01:06:32,322
until it manages that last... wriggle,

966
01:06:32,405 --> 01:06:34,199
that last push and it's out.

967
01:06:37,285 --> 01:06:42,207
Just what's it like now?
Do you look at it differently?

968
01:06:42,290 --> 01:06:45,710
One thing I'm really conscious of today
is how important family is.

969
01:06:45,793 --> 01:06:48,171
My parents stuck by me.
They loved me no matter what.

970
01:06:48,254 --> 01:06:49,756
My husband stood by me,

971
01:06:49,839 --> 01:06:54,135
and my children showed remarkable courage
and strength to come through all of that

972
01:06:54,219 --> 01:06:57,555
<i>to be the very wonderful adults</i>
<i>that they turned out to be.</i>

973
01:06:57,639 --> 01:07:00,975
<i>♪ To help pull me through ♪</i>

974
01:07:03,394 --> 01:07:05,063
<i>♪ Someday... ♪</i>

975
01:07:05,146 --> 01:07:07,106
[Sheela] <i>I have to live with myself.</i>

976
01:07:07,857 --> 01:07:13,363
And this living with myself,
I must look inside me.

977
01:07:13,446 --> 01:07:14,656
Who am I?

978
01:07:16,574 --> 01:07:17,951
What am I?

979
01:07:18,660 --> 01:07:19,953
Why am I?

980
01:07:21,371 --> 01:07:26,709
It is not good and bad,
right and wrong, black and white.

981
01:07:26,793 --> 01:07:33,216
Of course, I don't know
when I die I come in Hell or Heaven.

982
01:07:33,299 --> 01:07:34,592
But it doesn't matter.

983
01:07:34,676 --> 01:07:38,179
Wherever I come,
I will create my own paradise.

984
01:07:40,682 --> 01:07:43,434
<i>♪ Still trying to fix my mind ♪</i>

985
01:07:43,518 --> 01:07:46,145
<i>♪ I'm still trying to fix my mind ♪</i>

986
01:07:46,229 --> 01:07:48,982
<i>♪ My mind</i>
<i>My mind... ♪</i>

987
01:07:49,065 --> 01:07:50,358
[Sheela]
<i>I love my power.</i>

988
01:07:51,109 --> 01:07:52,026
<i>Why not?</i>

989
01:07:53,403 --> 01:07:56,823
Bhagwan has taught me strength.

990
01:07:58,449 --> 01:08:01,119
And you think I'm going
to waste my strength away?

991
01:08:14,090 --> 01:08:15,341
[Sheela]
<i>I would like to say...</i>

992
01:08:16,509 --> 01:08:18,803
<i>Sannyasin community,</i>

993
01:08:18,886 --> 01:08:25,143
you are negating
the whole experiment of Oregon

994
01:08:25,810 --> 01:08:30,523
by cutting it out
from Bhagwan's biography.

995
01:08:31,482 --> 01:08:35,069
<i>His lifetime dream was a new commune.</i>

996
01:08:36,279 --> 01:08:42,744
<i>And we created this beautiful community</i>
<i>that we lived in for years.</i>

997
01:08:43,953 --> 01:08:47,248
Don't kill him by concentrating...

998
01:08:48,041 --> 01:08:53,046
and feeling ashamed of... this scandal.

999
01:08:54,255 --> 01:09:00,511
Don't forget every one of us
was part of that scandal.

1000
01:09:05,058 --> 01:09:06,142
Finished?

1001
01:09:08,645 --> 01:09:09,771
Ah! [chuckles]

1002
01:09:09,854 --> 01:09:12,815
I thought
it would never come to an end in my life!

1003
01:09:12,899 --> 01:09:13,941
[laughs]

1004
01:09:16,778 --> 01:09:19,822
We definitely all need a drink.

1005
01:09:19,906 --> 01:09:21,324
Okay.

